@BOZX...perfect quality!!!

@black_skull530i - Thanks for all your help.  On my system PowerDVD 11 didn't play the ISO unless I accessed the specific file from the "video" tab. I am able to access the proper files directly from the DL without a virtual drive via the "video" tab and they play perfectly...including all of the extras.

@dududus - it took less than 20 min. to convert to an ISO via ImgBurn.  DL'ing an ISO file would require something like .rar files, and I personally would not DL a .rar movie...most of them are fakes.

Thanks again BOZX.
